hi, G., Effect of substrate and cellulase concentration on simultaneous saccharification and fermentation of steam-pretreated softwood for ethanol production (2000) Biotechnol Bioeng, 68, pp. 204-210; Stenberg, K., Galbe, M., Zacchi, G., The influence of lactic acid formation on the simultaneous saccharification and fermentation (SSF) of softwood to ethanol (2000) Enzyme Microb Technol, 26, pp. 71-79; Tengborg, C., Stenberg, K., Galbe, M., Zacchi, G., Larsson, S., Palmqvist, E., Hahn-Hägerdal, B., Comparison of SO2 and H 2SO4 impregnation of softwood prior to steam pretreatment on ethanol production (1998) Appl Biochem Biotechnol, 70-72, pp. 3-15; Tengborg, C., Galbe, M., Zacchi, G., Influence of enzyme loading and physical parameters on the enzymatic hydrolysis of steam-pretreated softwood (2001) Biotechnol Prog, 17, pp. 110-117; Tengborg, C., Galbe, M., Zacchi, G., Reduced inhibition of enzymatic hydrolysis of steam-pretreated softwood (2001) Enzyme Microb Technol, 28, pp. 835-844; Thomas, P.R., Infestation of pine and spruce bark beetles in British Columbia and its effect on kraft and mechanical pulping (1985) Harvesting and processing of beetle-killed timber. Proceedings of a Seminar, , Nielson RW, editor, 10 May, Prince George, BC, Canada. Vancouver: Forintek Canada Corp. Western Division; Westfall, J., (2004) 2004 Summary of forest, , health conditions in British Columbia; Wingren, A., Galbe, M., Roslander, C., Rudolf, A., Zacchi, G., Effect of reduction in yeast and enzyme concentrations in a simultaneous-saccharification- and-fermentation-based bioethanol process: Technical and economic evaluation (2005) Appl Biochem Biotechnol, 121-124, pp. 485-499; Wong, K.K.Y., Deverell, K.F., Mackie, K.L., Clark, T.A., Donaldson, L.A., The relationship between fiber porosity and cellulose digestibility in steam-exploded Pinus radiata (1988) Biotechnol Bioeng, 31, pp. 447-456; Wu, M.M., Chang, K., Gregg, D.J., Boussaid, A., Beatson, R.P., Saddler, J.N., Optimization of st